---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout title="Getting Started - Checkend">
  <header class="border-b border-gray-200">
    <nav class="mx-auto flex max-w-7xl items-center justify-between px-6 py-4 lg:px-8">
      <a href="/" class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">Checkend</a>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-6">
        <a href="/docs" class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-900">Docs</a>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/furvur/checkend"
          class="text-sm text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          GitHub
        </a>
      </div>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16 lg:px-8">
    <nav class="mb-8">
      <a href="/docs" class="text-sm text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-700">&larr; Back to Docs</a>
    </nav>

    <article class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">
      <h1>Getting Started</h1>

      <p>
        Checkend is a self-hosted error monitoring application. Follow these steps to get it running
        on your infrastructure.
      </p>

      <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Ruby 3.3+</li>
        <li>PostgreSQL 14+</li>
        <li>Node.js 20+ (for asset compilation)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Installation</h2>

      <h3>1. Clone the repository</h3>
      <pre
        class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 p-4 text-sm text-gray-100"><code>git clone https://github.com/furvur/checkend.git
cd checkend</code></pre>

      <h3>2. Install dependencies</h3>
      <pre class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 p-4 text-sm text-gray-100"><code>bundle install</code></pre>

      <h3>3. Set up the database</h3>
      <pre
        class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 p-4 text-sm text-gray-100"><code>bin/rails db:setup</code></pre>

      <h3>4. Start the server</h3>
      <pre class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 p-4 text-sm text-gray-100"><code>bin/dev</code></pre>

      <p>
        Visit <code>http://localhost:3000</code> to access the Checkend dashboard.
      </p>

      <h2>Deployment</h2>
      <p>
        Checkend includes Kamal configuration for easy deployment. See the
        <a href="/docs/deployment">deployment guide</a> for details.
      </p>

      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/docs/configuration">Configure your instance</a></li>
        <li><a href="/docs/api">Integrate the API</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
